Ford GoBike Dataset¶

by Caio Vasconcelos Silva Andrade¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

This notebook explores a dataset about the Ford Gobike system, a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area, now know as Bay Wheels, the dataset counts with 183412 values with features like gender, stations name and other ones

In [10]:
weekday = []

for i in df['start_time'].dt.dayofweek:
    if i == 0:
        weekday.append('Monday')
    elif i == 1:
        weekday.append('Tuesday')
    elif i == 2:
        weekday.append('Wednesday')
    elif i == 3:
        weekday.append('Thursday')
    elif i == 4:
        weekday.append('Friday')
    elif i == 5:
        weekday.append('Saturday')
    elif i == 6:
        weekday.append('Sunday')
In [11]:
a = np.array(weekday)
In [12]:
a = pd.Series(a)

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset have 183412 rows and 16 columns, i removed some rows with missing values, and some other cleaning...leaving us with 174874 rows, with columns like: 'duration_sec', 'start_time', 'end_time', 'start_station_id', 'start_station_name', 'start_station_latitude', 'start_station_longitude', 'end_station_id', 'end_station_name', 'end_station_latitude', 'end_station_longitude', 'bike_id', 'user_type', 'member_birth_year', 'member_gender', 'bike_share_for_all_trip'

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The main features of interest at least for me are: age, user type, gender, start and end station

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

Probably user_type, age, and gender will have effects on trip duration, stations and someother things. The dataset is about the San Francisco Area...i have never been to San Frasisco so maybe some research from my part about the stations names, just to see with they are really crowded or if there a University nearby...things like that!

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

  • The duration in secs of the trips are most of them in between 200 to 1000...meaning that most trip are less then 15 minutes! Which makes a lot of sense because this service works with single rides (up to 30 minutes);

  • We had a lot more males using this services;

  • A LOT more subscribers than normal customers.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

  • The main feature that i adjusted was the duration of the rent, where the only thing that i did was to "cut" the 15% highest values, because 85% of the trips were below 1000 secs;
  • The other thing i could have addressed was about the age, just subtract the birth year with the actual year...but i at the end i just leave as it is.
